1;fillColor=#e9b0a0;strokeColor=#b8402a;fontColor=#511810;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="977" y="752" width="272" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Meat-eater problem&lt;br&gt;(saved humans eat animals)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+5+8+9]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   73 lives-eq/$1k · 98% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Rainforest Trust · 2%&lt;br&gt;(Michael Dickens, Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + nature_intrinsic_value + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + suffering_focused + meat_eater_problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The meat-eater problem: a dollar of human global health also buys decades of that person&#x27;s meat consumption, and factory farming it causes suffering the animal circle now counts. Each present-human org is charged an additive penalty — farmed-animal life-years caused per human DALY, times the suffering per factory-farmed life-year, times the animal&#x27;s welfare range. Under a heavy animal welfare range the penalty can exceed the human benefit, so saving human lives looks net-harmful. Only bites once animals count, so it requires animals_somewhat; and it is a near-term human-vs-animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans), where x-risk dominates and the meat bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 8 suffering_focused → 9 meat_eater_problem" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJytWGtz27gV%2FSt3PN1WykoySb2dujPeWN5k6mQzttPMTpxRIBKSsOarAGlFzWZ%2Few8AUqJseq2O%2BiEeRgTOPffcBy747Sjgc5aH2ask4EcnR8fHdHp6SjeSiZiyhHzJ%2FrPGwyqm29xz3B6tEhkG94KvaOVOvWl32p%2BOpmNqqCxJadzU229jwJwplUdpJpKY%2FCXQTsihlMnEXwoWajB37JFLcyanbMXW02UesViVLzxisYhYqKYqifhqybLyTZdiluWST0WcSREr4U%2FvWZjz8n2f5rl5bwGnEcsyLqcrkS2ngVB%2BkseZiBfl8hGpfD7nQFpM54mfKx6Ur8YUcZZN8Q%2F7U5nMQh4Z1ybMXxLb%2BicUMXq%2FzpZ4nouQE7T